com.dukes.klein.scanner

Class AbstractToken<E extends Enum<E>,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dukes.klein.scanner.AbstractToken<E,V>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    KleinToken

    public abstract class AbstractToken<E extends Enum<E>,V>
extends Object

    Represents a token within a given grammar. The AbstractToken can be used to represent a token within any programming language.

    Since:
    0.1.0

    • Constructor Detail

      • AbstractToken

        protected AbstractToken()
        This is needed for an empty constructor to be present. This is made protected, as sublcasses don't inherit constructors.

      • AbstractToken

        protected AbstractToken(E tokenType,
                        V tokenValue)
        Constructs an AbstractToken with the token type describing what kind of token it is, while also describing the value of that token. Note: This does not actually construct an object. This and any other constructor in this class is used as a means to help subclasses conform to the standards of a Token.
        Parameters:
        tokenType - The type of token, as a value from an Enum
        tokenValue - The value of a token.

      • AbstractToken

        protected AbstractToken(E tokenType)
        Constructs an AbstractToken with the token type. The value of the token is null

    • Method Detail

        Determines whether this token is of the type provided.
        Parameters:
        tokenType - The type to compare to.
        Returns:
        true if the current token's tokenType is equivalent to the parameter, false otherwise.

      • toString

        public String toString()
        Shows the programmer a String representation of the AbstractToken. This is the tokentype as a string, followed by a tab and then the token value. If the token value is null, this method will exclude the tab and the token value.
        Overrides:
        toString in class Object
